                            <comment id="14193119" author="tilman" created="Sat, 1 Nov 2014 12:10:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Is this a bug report or an enhancement suggestion? If it is a bug, please post the exception stack trace and maybe attach a PDF that produces the exception. I haven&apos;t really understood what this issue is about. A good bug report contains 1) what did you do 2) what were you expecting 3) what happened.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14194656" author="lhuynh" created="Mon, 3 Nov 2014 16:03:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Signed PDF with image&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14194690" author="lhuynh" created="Mon, 3 Nov 2014 16:24:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi&lt;br/&gt;
I think this is a bug, but may be due to our  way to build a graphical signature.&lt;br/&gt;
As you can see in attached fichedescriptiveformulaire_8954_signed.pdf, the appearance dictionary is an indirect object :&lt;br/&gt;
/AP &amp;lt;&amp;lt;&lt;br/&gt;
/N 269 0 R&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
Without the modification, the exception was :&lt;br/&gt;
Caused by: java.lang.ClassCastException: org.apache.pdfbox.cos.COSObject cannot be cast to org.apache.pdfbox.cos.COSDictionary&lt;br/&gt;
	at org.apache.pdfbox.pdmodel.PDDocument.addSignature(PDDocument.java:487)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;About the NullPointerException (if (dr != null)), I don&apos;t remember in which case we got it, sorry.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Regards&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14194792" author="jahewson" created="Mon, 3 Nov 2014 17:55:00 +0000"  >&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;((COSObject) item).getObject();
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;There&apos;s no need to do COSObject dereferencing manually, just call getDictionaryObject() instead of getItem().&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;P.S. We should probably change those existing comments to English.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14196793" author="tilman" created="Tue, 4 Nov 2014 20:53:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Oops, now I see that the german is in our source code &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14196833" author="jira-bot" created="Tue, 4 Nov 2014 21:18:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Commit 1636738 from &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=tilman&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;tilman&quot;&gt;tilman&lt;/a&gt; in branch &apos;pdfbox/branches/1.8&apos;&lt;br/&gt;
[ &lt;a href=&quot;https://svn.apache.org/r1636738&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://svn.apache.org/r1636738&lt;/a&gt; ]&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-2470&quot; title=&quot;Exception in PDDocument.addSignature(PDSignature sigObject, SignatureInterface signatureInterface, SignatureOptions options))&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PDFBOX-2470&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PDFBOX-2470&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: translate comments, clean up code&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14196837" author="tilman" created="Tue, 4 Nov 2014 21:20:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Did you try Johns suggestion? I.e. change this:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;                        &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// read and set Appearance Dictionary
&lt;/span&gt;                        PDAppearanceDictionary ap = 
                                &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; PDAppearanceDictionary((COSDictionary)cosBaseDict.getItem(COSName.AP));
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;to this:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;                        PDAppearanceDictionary ap = 
                                &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; PDAppearanceDictionary((COSDictionary)cosBaseDict.getDictionaryObject(COSName.AP));
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14201895" author="lhuynh" created="Fri, 7 Nov 2014 10:25:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yes, I have tested and it works&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
